# =============================================================================
# TIPS FOR CUSTOMIZATION
# =============================================================================
# 1. Use specific patterns rather than broad ones when possible
# 2. Test your .gitignore with: git status --ignored
# 3. Use git check-ignore <file> to test specific files
# 4. Remember: .gitignore only affects untracked files
# 5. Use git rm --cached <file> to untrack already tracked files
# 6. Create global gitignore: git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore
# 7. Use ! to negate patterns and include specific files
